	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=67894"><span id="Scholar">Darknyss</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">550 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.01]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>At very high ATK values, you begin to see greater DPS through your weapons ratio than through the damage bonus.<br/><br/>However, in general, weapons with equal ratios will have their DPS dependant upon the Damage Bonus, especially since procs aren't effected by the speed of the weapon.<br/><br/>For 1-handers, there is a set dmg bonus that doesn't decrease, so you'll see dual-wielding classes that want the lowest delay to apply the damage bonus more often...<br/><br/>... but since 2-handers are given a much greater bonus for delay 28+, you really don't want to dip below that when looking for DPS, and you'll only draw more ripostes when tanking with a faster weapon as well.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Pain Lord Darknyss Grimscale<br/>70 Iksar Crusader of the Greenmist<br/></td></tr>
